Maverick entertainer and activist, CharlyBoy has advised Nigerians that the office of the citizen is bigger than the office of the President. CharlyBoy made this known in a post on his Twitter page on Sunday. He said the President and everyone in power are not Nigerians’ masters and for things to change in the country, Nigerians must understand that they are the government. “My fellow frustrated Nigerians. We must Understand say, The office of the Citizen us bigger than the office of the President. “Our rulers in power are not our Lord’s and Masters.Until we Understand say #nawebegovernment nothing will change in this country Nigeria,” he wrote. Meanwhile, the songwriter had last week vowed to dump Nigeria for Ghana. He made the vow while reacting to the emergence of former Vice President, Alhaji Atiku Abubakar and Asiwaju Ahmed Bola Tinubu as the presidential candidates of the two leading political parties in the land. The veteran musician feels the outcomes of both presidential primaries are no good news for Nigeria and Nigerians.